reviews_data.review_text: It’s a library, with books, and comfy chairs, and study tables, and Wifi. Bathrooms were clean. Moderate background noise for a busy spot. It appeared safe and well staffed.
Love it here. Not too busy and always a spot to study.
Nice library, don’t ask why I searched up evil jonkler cart 😭🙏
Love the layout and space to sit for reading or doing homework. Nice neighborhood library. Friendly staff. Great for the entire family.
Очень приятное место,для досуга...
We are fortunate to have an amazing library here in Matthews.  Great for children and adults!

First time at this library and was pleasantly surprised to see how big and active it was on a Saturday morning. Came for their Paws to Read event. My son picked out a book to read to a volunteer dog for 15 minutes. It was very cute and nice for him to practice his reading with a furry friend. They have children's sections with plenty of children's books, and computers for them to play on. They have a language section with Spanish, French, and Asian books which I thought was neat. They have a teens section with a bunch of young adult books, activities, and games to play with. I do see they have a lot of events during the week also so I will be checking those out. They have plenty of parking spaces around the library and side street parking. We will be visiting a lot more often during the summer. All employees are super friendly and knowledgeable.
I didn't go here, but I had to rate it or Google will keep asking.

My favorite library in all of Charlotte!! I’ve been coming for eleven years now, and it’s always been a pleasant experience. Last week on my most recent trip Kaia was so helpful helping me get a new card and putting a book on hold at a different location. She was very efficient and helpful and kind!! Thank you!!
The library is fantastic

It is a lovely place to be.
Debbie is amazing, she helped us to get our library cards and explained all the programs.

I wanted to praise the children's librarians for the amazing job they do with storytime always keeping the children and adults entertained I did not appreciate when one of the librarians said we should only attend one storytime a week the library is a free program and we should be allowed to attend as many times as we please

Very friendly staff! A wide collection of books and tables to study or play a board game on like chess or monopoly. It had adult and children books with a children's area in the corner for them to play in and some shelves with history of the town of Matthews. Sometimes it can be loud and the employees don't tell them to quiet down they just look at them but they did help a little girl find her dad!

This library is way too small and underfunded for the community it serves. There are often long wait lists for the most popular books and resources. The last several times I’ve gone to the Matthews library to check out a book I had to wait over a month for one to become available. I’m not talking about some rare book with only a few copies in print, these were popular books with millions of copies in print worldwide, just not here apparently. Both times I ended up ordering the books on Amazon for less than $20 and they arrived at my house in a few days.  Perfect example, for one particular resource I am currently #45 on the waitlist for 25 available copies. Charlotte Mecklenburg Library is quickly becoming irrelevant in my opinion.
I love this library. I often rented rooms to have meetups with my group and often spent time browsing their books. Great selection and great meeting rooms

Wonderful local library located in downtown Matthews. Very large library with computers, computer rooms, children's library with activities for the kids, music CDs and movie DVDs available to sign out, and a super friendly and knowledgeable staff. We are so fortunate to have such a valuable resource as our Matthews library. Please patronize it when you can. It's such a huge asset to our local community.
Great place to take the kids! Lots of books and many cozy places to sit and read for the kiddos.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We love Matthews and are glad you do too!

reviews_data.review_text: This is absolutely my fave library in the Meck Co area. It's spacious, well lit, friendly staff and they host so many classes for kids as well as adults. I was here recently for a woven jewelry class. It was totally free and so much fun. I've never woven a thing in my life, so to learn something new today and free at that made it even more awesome.
Storytime here is so fun! The staff is great
Beautiful location, knowledgeable and friendly staff. A pleasure to visit.
Love books. This is great. I will be coming soon!!

I have been going to  the Chatlotte Meck- Matthews library branch for almost 10 years and I absolutely love the environment. The employees are professional , resourceful and well trained.  Another thing I love is their location in dowtown and most of all is the fireplace on cold days,  all you need is hot chocolate  with marshmallows. Its also a great environment for children and they have lots of educational resources. This is my place of peace and calm.👍🏾
Love the Railroad Decor!
Such a sweet space, the train theme, the history of Matthews mural, butterflies, houseplants looking so happy, the fireplace, Matthews is one to see!
Great little library!! Lots of services available. Super, high-tech checkouts. Great atmosphere and TONS of children's books.
Library and voting were excellent
Love the library in Matthews! My granddaughter had a ball today reading to me, we did the scavenger hunt (spiders) And she learns on the computers. Everyone is friendly and knowledgeable. Thank you!
This is a nice, medium-sized library with books you can borrow (they call it "check out"). Good selection of kids' books. Sci-fi and fantasy genres are a little lacking.
Love the Matthews Library! So easy to place my books on hold, run in to grab, self checkout, and then I'm out. Thank you all for making reading so accessible to everyone!
The people were nice and welcoming. The atmosphere was quiet and relaxing as a library should be. Parking was easy and free.
Library staff was helpful

reviews_data.review_text:
I stopped by to print something I needed to be notarized. I didn't have my library card on me. I explained the situation to the 1st young lady at the door & she directed me to the Information Desk.

The young lady there was also helpful, explaining how I could log on as a guest to do what I needed done. She also offered to look up my library card info & assisted me with paying for my printed copies via card. Usually a great experience here.
Full of books complete with a restroom if you need it while raiding in Pokémon Go on Wednesday nights. Lol
Love this library....our grandchildren (10,8, and 6) always feel so at home and can't wait to see what books they'll find
Great experience at the library. Super selection on books. Today I did print outs and it was very easy and quick. Friendly stuff at all times.
First time here and it was very nice. Very friendly staff.
It was amazing and has alot books my kids like.
The staff are very polite and helpful..💖💯🙏
The easiest passport renewal ever
We loved visiting this branch everyone is so nice.  Take the children across the street to the train for some nice pics
Easy in and out. Liked the self checkout station.

Wesley the manger there went above and beyond.  With Covid the new way of life changes daily it seems.  Well,  I had reserved books online to pick up at the Library.  They now have them in the lobby to pick up.  Today I had a young man with a wheel chair with me.  It was going to take more time getting him in and out of the car than if someone could bring them out.  Well, Wesley the manager was happy to bring out our books.  He came out, and only had cds.  I am new to the checking out online.  Wesley was more than happy to go get the books and check them out for us.  He brought them out to our truck.  Thank You Wesley, you set the example of great customer service.
Alsome.this place has a large variety of books everything you looking for, every body is respectful and nice will be back ASAP
Love this library.
Great Customer service!
I accidentally checked out the wrong book, and the staff were kind enough to take time out of their duties to get the right book. Awesome staff!!
Books man
So grateful that the libraries have reopened!
Great place 2 work and read
Very cozy. Love going to study!!!

We love this library! The staff is friendly! This is the cutest little area. Great place to come enjoy a morning & story time with your kids. The last two we have been to were awesome!  Great children’s play area & selection of children’s books! We recently went to an inter generational story time and the kids I watch really enjoyed it we sang, danced and made crafts! We hope they do it again soon!

One of the loudest libraries, kids running around, adults having personal phone conversations. When this was mentioned to a staff member she just chuckled. I thought the purpose of a library was to work in silence!!!! AWFUL!!

We have used the programs and services at this library for over 7 years. My children love this library's child section and play area. We come weekly to get books (child and adult), play, and see what new programs they are offering for all ages. My oldest has used their Reading Buddies and Paws to Read programs. Both of my children have at various times participated in Storytimes and the Active Reading programs. The resources for individuals and families are excellent. The librarians I've spoken with have always been enthusiastic and helpful. I appreciate having such an excellent library in my community. Thank you so much!
Awesome Staff!!! Very friendly, helpful, always available and very knowledgeable!!! The parking is also a plus and the library is huge and very clean!! This is honestly the BEST Library!

The best library ever! The baby and family Storytimes are the best.  The storytimes are all expertly led and have a wonderful theme each time.  After stories and songs, they do bubbles and bring out a giant box of toys.  Amazing staff and great programs for all.  There is even a play area for kids with lots of fun toys.
Thank you for having this as a resource for parents in the community!
Very nice library and staff.
Always clean, friendly staff, and storytime for kids :) keep it up!
A welcoming public library with events for all ages.
Our absolute favorite library. Always clean and organized. Probably one of the best kid centers  we’ve seen at a public library
This library is really nice. Staff is friendly and very helpful. Kids corner is lovely, kids go to the library with pleasure. If they could they would go there everyday.
Very nice and cosy. And plenty of parking space around and staff is very helpful.
Vote+
Staff very knowledgeable and always willing to help.

Books are the quietest and most constant of friends: they are the most accessible and wisest of counsellors, and the most patient of teachers.
Charles W. Eliot
Clean quality library along with very personable, knowledgeable and helpful staff.
很漂亮，
Great Customer Service
Very helpful and friendly people. I would suggest hanging out here with a good book or two. Many people don't know about all the awesome resources here! Use them!

I spend about 50% of my time working from home and started using this library when I moved to Matthews a few months ago. The staff are super friendly, the atmosphere is comfortable, quiet, and a perfect place for me to settle in when I've got hours and hours of spreadsheets to review! The only reason I'm giving 4 stars and not 5 is because the Wi-Fi connection can be inconsistent at times. Otherwise, it's a great local resource!!

I have been coming to this library since I was young and have always adored it. Very clean, cozy, and comfy with a huge selection of all kinds of books. It's a great place to get work done or just hang out and relax. I could spend hours in here!
Staff is nice. Library clean. Always enjoy visiting.
Great library. My daughter enjoys going there on a weekly basis.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you - we hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Pretty good selection of books and movies. Clean. I'd give it four stars but the staff usually glares and rarely says hi. There are a few that are friendly but not the majority.
Nice :3
